perform (sth) or bring (sth) to completion 履行（某事）；使（某事）实现：
fulfil a promise, prophecy 履行诺言、使预言实现。
satisfy (sth); answer 满足（某事）；符合：
fulfil a desire, prayer, hope, need, dream, etc满足欲望、实现祈愿、符合愿望、符合需要、符合理想
Does your job fulfil your expectations? 你的工作符合你的预想吗?
satisfy the specific requirements of (sth) 满足（某事）的要求：
fulfil the terms of a contract满足合同条款的要求
fulfil the conditions of entry to a university 具备某大学的入学条件。
perform (sth); do; obey fully 履行（某事）；做；服从：
fulfil a duty, a command, an obligation, etc 履行职责、服从命令、履行义务。
fulfil oneself fully develop one's abilities and character 充分发挥自己的能力和性格：
He was able to fulfil himself through music.他通过音乐能充分地发挥自己的才能。
fulfilled
adj
satisfied; completely happy 满意的；满足的；十分愉快的：
He doesn't feel really fulfilled in his present job.他对目前的工作并非真正满意。
fulfilment
n
Ufulfilling or being fulfilled 满意；满足。
